---
// AboutSection.astro — Module B
// Static: intellectual narrative constrained to max-w-[600px]
// No JS — pure HTML/CSS
---

<section
  id="about"
  aria-labelledby="about-heading"
  class="relative px-6 py-24 flex justify-center"
>
  <div class="flex flex-col gap-12 w-full max-w-[600px]">
    <!-- Section heading — h2 for correct heading hierarchy (H1 in Hero → H2 here) -->
    <h2
      id="about-heading"
      class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-[var(--color-text-muted)] font-normal"
    >
      About
    </h2>

    <!-- Narrative prose -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 text-base leading-[1.8] text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
      <p>
        I've spent over a decade learning how software really works — not just
        how to write it, but how to architect it so that future engineers (and
        future me) can reason about it without pain.
      </p>

      <p>
        My work centers on <span class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">clean architecture</span>,
        domain-driven thinking, and building interfaces that don't apologize for
        existing. I care deeply about what happens after the MVP: maintenance,
        extensibility, the human cost of complexity.
      </p>

      <p>
        I teach because I believe most engineering problems are communication
        problems. The gap between "it works" and "it's good" is almost always
        conceptual, not technical. I try to close that gap — with teams, with
        content, with open-source tools.
      </p>

      <p>
        Currently obsessed with AI-assisted workflows, keyboard-driven
        development environments, and making Neovim feel like a tailored suit.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Divider -->
    <div
      class="w-12 border-t border-[var(--color-glass-border)]"
      aria-hidden="true"
    ></div>

    <!-- Sparse factual line -->
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-x-6 gap-y-2 text-xs tracking-wider uppercase text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
      <span>Barcelona, Spain</span>
      <span class="text-[var(--color-glass-border)]">·</span>
      <span>TypeScript · Go · Lua</span>
      <span class="text-[var(--color-glass-border)]">·</span>
      <span>Clean / Hexagonal Architecture</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
